    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix double scaling issue in IDFT implementations\n\n### Summary\nThe IDFT implementations for sizes 512, 1024, and 768 in the PHY layer were applying scaling factors twice during computation. This occurred because the sub-DFT functions (idft256) were called with scale=1, applying their own scaling, and then the parent functions applied additional scaling. This double scaling resulted in incorrect output values that were half of the expected magnitude.\n\nThe issue was particularly noticeable in idft1024() where the output values were consistently scaled down by a factor of 2. The fix modifies the scale parameter passed to idft256() sub-function calls from 1 to 0, ensuring that only the final scaling in the parent functions is applied.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/TOOLS/oai_dfts.c`: \n  - Modified idft512() to call idft256() with scale=0 instead of scale=1\n  - Modified idft1024() to call idft256() with scale=0 instead of scale=1  \n  - Modified idft768() to call idft256() with scale=0 instead of scale=1\n  - Fixed formatting issues (tabs to spaces) throughout the file\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Call idft1024() with any input data\n2. Observe that the output values are half of what they should be\n3. Compare with expected mathematical IDFT results\n4. The same issue can be observed in idft512() and idft768() functions\n\nThe fix ensures that these functions now produce output values with the correct magnitude.\n"
}